🌍 Project Overview

NewsHub is a dynamic and fully responsive news web application that allows users to explore the latest global headlines from trusted news sources in real-time.
Powered by the News API, this application fetches and displays breaking news, top stories, and user-searched articles in a visually appealing layout.

The goal of this project is to demonstrate API integration, frontend design, and backend interaction using modern web development technologies such as HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and PHP.

✨ Key Features

✅ Fetches real-time news articles from News API
✅ Search functionality to find news by topic or keyword (e.g., “International News”)
✅ Displays title, description, image, and link for each article
✅ Beautiful, responsive UI designed using Bootstrap and CSS
✅ Dynamic content loading using JavaScript fetch requests
✅ Backend integration (PHP) for improved data handling and security
✅ Error handling for failed API requests or empty results
✅ Compatible with all modern browsers and screen sizes

🧠 Learning Objectives

This project helped in practicing and understanding:

How to fetch data from external APIs

How to structure and style web content using HTML5, CSS3, and Bootstrap

How to handle dynamic data rendering with JavaScript

How to integrate a simple PHP backend

How to maintain clean and modular code

