⚙️ Setup and Installation Guide

Follow these steps to set up and run the project locally:

1️⃣ Clone the Repository
git clone https://github.com/your-username/NewsHub.git

2️⃣ Move Project to Server Directory

If using XAMPP, move the project folder into:

C:\xampp\htdocs\

3️⃣ Start the Server

Open XAMPP Control Panel

Start Apache (for PHP)

4️⃣ Get Your API Key

Visit https://newsapi.org/

Create a free account and generate an API key

Copy the API key

5️⃣ Add the API Key

In your app.js or backend.php, locate the section where the API call is made and replace:

const apiKey = "YOUR_API_KEY_HERE";


with your actual key.

6️⃣ Run the App

Open your browser and visit:

http://localhost/NewsHub/

7️⃣ Use the Application

Type any keyword (e.g., “International News”, “Sports”, “Technology”) in the search bar

Press Enter or click “Search” to fetch live articles instantly

📂 Project Structure
NewsHub/
│
├── index.html          # Main HTML file (Home Page)
├── style.css           # Custom styles (includes animations and responsiveness)
├── app.js              # JavaScript file (API integration + UI rendering)
├── backend.php         # PHP backend for handling API requests securely
├── assets/             # Folder for images, icons, etc.
└── README.md           # Project documentation file

💡 Future Improvements

🚀 The project can be enhanced in the following ways:

Add category filters (e.g., Business, Sports, Entertainment)

Include dark mode / light mode toggle

Enable saving favorite articles locally using localStorage or database

Add user authentication to create personalized news feeds

Integrate pagination or infinite scroll for smoother browsing

Use database caching to reduce API requests

